Policy.acknowledgement_statement: Funding support for the DETECT (DEvelopmental TrajECtories Twins) study: “Genomics of Developmental Trajectories in Twins” (parent study: Netherlands Twin Register (NTR)) was provided by the Netherlands Organization for Scientific Research (NWO) and MagW/ZonMW grants 912-10-020, 463-06-001, 451-04-034, 400-05-717, Spi-56-464-14192, Center for Medical Systems Biology (CSMB, NWO Genomics), Biobanking and Biomolecular Resources Research Infrastructure (BBMRI –NL, 184.021.007); by the VU University Institute for Health and Care Research (EMGO+ ), the Neuroscience Campus Amsterdam (NCA); the European Science Council (ERC 230374) and the Avera Institute, Sioux Falls, South Dakota (USA) . The dataset(s) used for the analyses described in this manuscript were obtained from the database of Genotypes and Phenotypes (dbGaP) found at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gap through dbGaP accession number phs000520.v1.p1. Samples and associated phenotype data for the DETECT study (PI: Dr. JJ Hudziak MD) were provided by Dr. Dorret I. Boomsma, PhD and Dr. Eco de Geus, PhD VU University Amsterdam (PIs NTR).
